1. Clone the repository
Open your terminal or Termux app and run:
git clone https://github.com/ECOhotz27/ecoScan4x.git

2. Change directory
Navigate into the project folder:
cd ecoScan4x

3. Run the tool
Make sure you have Python installed. If youâ€™re using Termux, you can install Python with:
pkg install python

Run the scanner on a URL:
python3 ecoScan4x.py https://example.com
Or run it with a file containing multiple URLs:
python3 ecoScan4x.py targets.txt

4. Check results
Results are saved automatically in the project folder as TXT, JSON, and CSV files after the scan completes.
